<ul class="task-constraints">
<li><b>Time limit:</b> 1.00 s</li>
<li><b>Memory limit:</b> 512 MB</li>
</ul>
<input type="hidden" name="course" value="problemset">
<input type="hidden" name="task" value="1085">
You are given an array containing $n$ positive integers.<br />
<br />
Your task is to divide the array into $k$ subarrays so that the maximum sum in a subarray is as small as possible.<br />
<br />
<b id="input">Input</b><br />
<br />
The first input line contains two integers $n$ and $k$: the size of the array and the number of subarrays in the division.<br />
<br />
The next line contains $n$ integers $x_1,x_2,\ldots,x_n$: the contents of the array.<br />
<br />
<b id="output">Output</b><br />
<br />
Print one integer: the maximum sum in a subarray in the optimal division.<br />
<br />
<b id="constraints">Constraints</b><br />
<ul>
<li>$1 \le n \le 2 \cdot 10^5$<br />
<li>$1 \le k \le n$<br />
<li>$1 \le x_i \le 10^9$<br />
</ul>
<b id="example">Example</b><br />
<br />
Input:<br />
<code>5 3<br />
2 4 7 3 5</code><br />
<br />
Output:<br />
<code>8</code><br />
<br />
Explanation: An optimal division is $[2,4],[7],[3,5]$ where the sums of the subarrays are $6,7,8$. The largest sum is the last sum $8$.    </div>
